## What factors led to these results?  ...    ensure grid reliability. This year’s PRA results demonstrated that most zones across the MISO region have sufficient  ...    It’s important for organizations to understand that while pricing may look one way one year, it could look completely  ...    * All Zones: capacity prices for the Summer roughly tripled to $30/MW-day  ...    deflation and market stabilization as we approach 2025/2026. Our team analyzed MISO PRA pricing in 3 regions –Zone 4 (Illinois), Zone 5 (Missouri), and Zone 7 (Michigan) from the 2019/2020 delivery year to the 2024/2025 delivery year.  ...    This chart shows the boom-and-bust nature of the MISO PRA prices. This boom-and-bust nature is due, in part, to the auction mechanics of the PRA. The auction uses a nearly vertical demand curve –meaning there is very little value  ...    MISO’s PRA results offer valuable insights into the complexities of the energy market, highlighting the importance of  ...    response in MISO.\n#### Learn more about advancing your energy strategy by leveraging our integrated energy solutions. Contact our team today\n## Related insights\n\nBlog  ...    IconChevron IconClose IconAdd IconIncrease IconArrow Oblique IconArrow Down IconSearch Iconicons.alternativeSearch.titleicons.alternativeSearch.descShare IconFilter IconEmail iconIcon Email OutlineIcon  ...    Down OutlineIcon PhoneIcon EmergencyIcon Thumb Downicons-list-view-title"
